<subSubSection id="B226D830C9F7D703FBD4584B244A7451" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="588BB6F5C2AB48008FB8698AB00ADE1D" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3379B8E879C36F9F85D9DF2D91D077" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
Mae Chaem district, Doi Inthanon NP (Chiang Mai province); 
<bibRefCitation id="CBC21840C238B0C2DA4D5F5454A1E089" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Reichenbachia" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 14" title="Neue Eintagsfliegen aus Thailand, nebst einigen Bemerkungen zu deren generischem Status (Insecta, Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae)." volume="28" year="1990">Braasch (1990)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="110462E090B9DFD50EA372A9306747A8" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus aculeatus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">Epeorus aculeatus</taxonomicName>
from Doi Inthanon National Park, Chiang Mai province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5E6F6CDBE247C2D8BA5DB37F0AD1A9A5" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="145E999D370F243E4681F5DC135245A8" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8FDA9C7DB8585CD6473F601861D5EA5" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
The larva of 
<taxonomicName id="55E865115DB695B64149EF9658DAE865" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus aculeatus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">Epeorus aculeatus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from that of othercongeners by abdominal terga 2-9 (Fig. 1A) each bearing a pair of long, acute, submedian spines on its posterior margin, and with a median dark brown spot on femoral surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BE7FBDFF429666CD845C9528B1C2C622" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" type="habitat and biology">
<paragraph id="53F18C68E03658C94E0B24FCAE3B27B3" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Habitat and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1BF43BD581FEDDA1ABAE98373DE0D257" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
The larva of 
<taxonomicName id="3F3B0AB13BCC88F835C4295617056204" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus aculeatus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">Epeorus aculeatus</taxonomicName>
occurs in headwater streams between 600-740 m alt in Thailand and high mountain streams between 1,400-2,800 m in Vietnam (
<bibRefCitation id="4495B74C111016A3CD4FAF0009A6D05A" author="Nguyen, VV" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology" pageId="27" pageNumber="88" pagination="19 - 28" title="Larvae of the heptageniid mayfly genus Epeorus (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae) from Vietnam." volume="7" year="2004 a">Nguyen and Bae 2004a</bibRefCitation>
). The larvae are mostly found under rocks in fast flowing reaches of the streams. The substrate consists of mixed sand/gravel and larger stones such as boulders and cobble.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9DC8B7B654D85539AD69882635CFCE21" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="5B1C596C67D221C04606167CEA7ABC58" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A9E65D83943E16C94F1044331DC51E6" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<bibRefCitation id="881128A52FEC266CF1FDD26650273ACC" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Reichenbachia" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 14" title="Neue Eintagsfliegen aus Thailand, nebst einigen Bemerkungen zu deren generischem Status (Insecta, Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae)." volume="28" year="1990">Braasch (1990)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on larval specimens. Then, 
<bibRefCitation id="0297F4E95FEB6CD583606BF2B9C53DFD" author="Webb, JM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="28" pageNumber="89" pagination="65 - 68" title="First description of the adult male of Epeorus aculeatus Braasch (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae)." volume="1277" year="2006">Webb and McCafferty (2006)</bibRefCitation>
described the male imago of 
<taxonomicName id="3D118622328D1C9CCF52BBD64601B6BA" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus aculeatus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">Epeorus aculeatus</taxonomicName>
based on reared Thai specimens from Doi Suthep NP, Chiangmai province. This species is different from other known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="EE28DA06E50E3D9D1FCF8203A3266E93" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
by each bearing a pair of long, acute, submedian spines on its posterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
